{"overview":"This compact B major waltz unfolds in a clear ternary (ABA') design, remaining harmonically stable throughout but enriched by a modal mixture stroke—the striking iv chord (E minor) within an otherwise diatonic B major palette—and a colorful raised-II (C double-sharp/Neapolitan-adjacent) in the varied return that gives the coda its expressive weight. The most distinctive feature is the interplay between the lyrical B section's sustained pedal-point countermelody and the modal inflections of the A sections, lending the piece a bittersweet intimacy despite its dance-like 3/4 framework.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","modal_mixture","pedal_point","neapolitan","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","meditative","intimate"]}
